org.strongback.command

Class ControllerCommand

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.strongback.command.Command
      • org.strongback.command.ControllerCommand
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    UnmanagedControllerCommand

    public class ControllerCommand
extends Command
    A command that uses the supplied Controller to move toward the controller's target. The controller is assumed to operate automatically and continuously, independently of this command. For example, it might be a hardware-based controller (e.g., PID control on the Talon SRX), or a software-based controller (e.g., SoftwarePIDController) that is registered with Strongback's executor to run in the background. (See UnmanagedControllerCommand for a command that will explicitly run the controller only when commands use it.)

    Although this command can be used directly via Command.reuse(Controller, Runnable), it is also designed to be subclassed to create custom, reusable, and concrete commands tailored for your robot. Typically this involves only defining custom public constructors to make the commands easy to use, and inheriting all other functionality.

    See Also:
    Command.reuse(Controller, Runnable), Command.reuse(double, Controller, Runnable), UnmanagedControllerCommand

    • Constructor Detail

      • ControllerCommand

        protected ControllerCommand(Controller sharedController,
                            Runnable initializer,
                            Requirable... requirements)
        Create a command that uses the given shared and managed controller to move within the controller's tolerance of the target. The initializer can be used to update the controller's target, tolerance, and any other controller settings when the command is initialized.
        Parameters:
        sharedController - the PID+FF controller; may not be null
        initializer - the controller initialization function, which should update the controller's target, tolerance, and any other setting; may be null
        requirements - the Requirables this Command requires

      • ControllerCommand

        protected ControllerCommand(double timeoutInSeconds,
                            Controller sharedController,
                            Runnable initializer,
                            Requirable... requirements)
        Create a command that uses the given shared and managed controller to move within the controller's tolerance of the target, timing out if the command takes longer than durationInSeconds. The initializer can be used to update the controller's target, tolerance, and any other controller settings when the command is initialized.
        Parameters:
        timeoutInSeconds - how long in seconds this command executes before terminating, zero is forever
        sharedController - the shared controller; may not be null
        initializer - the controller initialization function, which should update the controller's target, tolerance, and any other setting; may be null
        requirements - the Requirables this Command requires

        public final void initialize()
        Description copied from class: Command
        Perform a one-time setup of this Command prior to any calls to Command.execute(). No physical hardware should be manipulated.

        By default this method does nothing.

        initialize in class Command

      • preExecute

        protected void preExecute()
        Called one time at the end of initialize(), after the initializer has run and after the controller has been enabled. This method does nothing by default, but can be overridden in subclasses for specific behavior.

      • end

        public void end()
        Description copied from class: Command
        Perform one-time clean up of the resources used by this command and typically putting the robot in a safe state. This method is always called after Command.execute() returns true unless Command.interrupted() is called.

        By default this method does nothing.
